==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[frictio]]''', from perfect passive participle '''[[frictus]]'''

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/fɹɪkʃən̩/}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪkʃən|-ɪkʃən]]

===Noun===
'''friction'''  ([[uncountable]])

# The [[rubbing]] of one [[object]] or [[surface]] against another.
# [[Conflict]], as between persons having [[dissimilar]] [[ideas]] or [[interests]]; [[clash]].
# {{cattag|Physics}}: A [[force]] that [[resist]]s the [[relative]] [[motion]] or [[tendency]] to such motion of two [[bodies]] in [[contact]].

